MUST FEATURES — Functional Requirements
1. Input Form (Subjects & Marks)
User Actions:
User enters their name (optional)
User inputs subjects and corresponding marks
User clicks the "Analyze" button
System Behavior:
System collects all entered data
Validates input (marks should be numbers, not empty)
Data Processing:
Store subjects and marks in a structured format
Expected Output:
Valid data is sent to the analysis module
Error message shown if input is invalid

2. Performance Analysis
User Actions:
Triggered after user submits data
System Behavior:
System evaluates marks:
< 50 → Weak
50–75 → Average
> 75 → Strong
Data Processing:
Loop through each subject and assign category
Expected Output:
Categorized list of subjects

3. Results Display
User Actions:
User views results
System Behavior:
System displays categorized results clearly
Expected Output:
Strengths, Weaknesses, Average sections

4. Improvement Suggestions
System Behavior:
Generate suggestions based on weak subjects
Expected Output:
Simple improvement tips